<div class="article-headline" id="Headline">LEMON COCONUT STACK CAKES</div>



<div class="article-in-image" id="image1"><img src="images/page038.article002.image1.jpg" class="article-in-image" alt=""/></div>
<div id="separatorLine"> <div class="invisible">empty</div> </div>

<div class="articleImageCredit" id="ImageCredit">PHOTOGRAPHY BY WILLIAM DICKEY</div>
<div class="article-body" id="Body"><p class="no-indent">Makes about 2 dozen </p><br/><p class="no-indent">1 (16-ounce) box pound cake mix </p><p class="no-indent">¼ cup softened butter </p><p class="no-indent">½ cup milk </p><p class="no-indent">2 large eggs </p><p class="no-indent">2 teaspoons lemon zest </p><p class="no-indent">3 tablespoons fresh lemon juice </p><p class="no-indent">1 (3.4-ounce) box instant coconut cream pudding mix </p><p class="no-indent">1½ cups heavy whipping cream </p><p class="no-indent">1 cup sour cream </p><p class="no-indent">Garnish: toasted coconut </p><br/><p class="no-indent">1. Preheat oven to 350°. Spray a 15x10-inch jelly-roll pan with nonstick baking spray with flour. </p><br/><p class="no-indent">2. In a large bowl, beat pound cake mix and next 5 ingredients at medium speed with a mixer until smooth. Pour into prepared pan. </p><br/><p class="no-indent">3. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Let cool in pan for 1 hour. </p><br/><p class="no-indent">4. In a medium bowl, beat pudding mix, cream, and sour cream at medium speed with a mixer for 2 minutes or until very thick. </p><br/><p class="no-indent">5. Using a 1-inch round cutter, cut cake into rounds. Slice each round in half cross-wise. Spoon or pipe about 1 tablespoon pudding mixture on bottom half of each cake round. Cover with cake round tops. Spoon or pipe about 1 teaspoon pudding mixture on top cake round. Garnish with toasted coconut, if desired.</p></div>
